Mmusi Maimane says the Public Protector&#8217;s State of Capture report exposes what he calls the rot within the ANC. BRAAMFONTEIN Democratic Alliance (DA) leader Mmusi Maimane says the removal of President Jacob Zuma is only the beginning of tackling corruption adding that the African National Congress (ANC) is not separate from Zuma. Maimane was joined by mayors Herman Mashaba, Patricia de Lille and Solly Msimanga at a media briefing in Johannesburg today to give feedback following the party s two day federal council meeting. The two Gauteng mayors gave feedback on their challenges taking over two of the biggest metros.The DA leader says the Public Protector s State of Capture report exposes what he calls the rot within the ANC. The ANC and Jacob Zuma are one, Zuma is not an exception within the ANC. He is the ANC, therefore the ANC can t self-correct, it s beyond repair and has indeed entered its final hour. He says a motion of no confidence will be debated in Parliament in the coming days in efforts to have the president removed. Maimane called on outspoken ANC members such as Jackson Mthembu to do more than call out the ruling party in the media.